The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Friday, September 17, 2004 

 London: Belgiums Kim Clijsters and Australian Lleyton Hewitt, the golden couple of tennis, will marry next February in Australia.

 Clijsters, 21, said on her website on Thursday that a party for their close friends would be held in a Belgian chateau after the wedding.

 Sao Paulo: Three-time French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten has said that he is undergoing new medical tests to decide if he needs more surgery on a recurring hip injury. Kuerten underwent surgery on the same hip in February 2002 but has since struggled to regain the form. 

 London: Hungary?s Robert Fazekas has launched a bid to have his Olympic discus gold medal returned, the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) said on Thursday. Fazekas was stripped of his medal at the Athens Games last month for failing to provide a complete urine sample.

